It said that the new visa regime starts from March 1, 2023, adding that it would apply to Nigerians who want to enter the United States temporarily for business and/or tourism. The United States Government has announced that it will increase visitor visa validity from 24 months to 60 months for Nigerians.
It said that the new visa regime starts from March 1, 2023, adding that it would apply to Nigerians who want to enter the United States temporarily for business and/or tourism.
The visa validity extension allows Nigerians to use the visa for 60 months to make short trips to the United States for tourism or business purposes before having to renew their visa.  
The visa application fee, currently USD160, will not increase as a result of the increased visa validity.